{"title": "Emotional consequences of COVID-19 home confinement: The ECLB-COVID19 multicenter study", "authors": [{"first": "Achraf", "last": "Ammar"}, {"first": "Patrick", "last": "Mueller"}, {"first": "Khaled", "last": "Trabelsi"}, {"first": "Hamdi", "last": "Chtourou"}, {"first": "Omar", "last": "Boukhris"}, {"first": "Liwa", "last": "Masmoudi"}, {"first": "Bassem", "last": "Bouaziz"}, {"first": "Michael", "last": "Brach"}, {"first": "Marlen", "last": "Schmicker"}, {"first": "Ellen", "last": "Bentlage"}, {"first": "Daniella", "last": "How"}, {"first": "Mona", "last": "Ahmed"}, {"first": "Asma", "last": "Aloui"}, {"first": "Omar", "last": "Hammouda"}, {"first": "Laisa Liane", "last": "Paineiras-Domingos"}, {"first": "Annemarie", "last": "Braakman-jansen"}, {"first": "Christian", "last": "Wrede"}, {"first": "Sophia", "last": "Bastoni"}, {"first": "Carlos", "last": "Soares Pernambuco"}, {"first": "Leonardo", "last": "Mataruna"}, {"first": "Morteza", "last": "Taheri"}, {"first": "Khadijeh", "last": "Irandoust"}, {"first": "Aïmen", "last": "Khacharem"}, {"first": "Nicola L", "last": "Bragazzi"}, {"first": "Karim", "last": "Chamari"}, {"first": "Jordan M", "last": "Glenn"}, {"first": "Nicholas T", "last": "Bott"}, {"first": "Faiez", "last": "Gargouri"}, {"first": "Lotfi", "last": "Chaari"}, {"first": "Hadj", "last": "Batatia"}, {"first": "Gamal Mohamed", "last": "Ali"}, {"first": "Osama", "last": "Abdelkarim"}, {"first": "Mohamed", "last": "Jarraya"}, {"first": "Kais El", "last": "Abed"}, {"first": "Nizar", "last": "Souissi"}, {"first": "Lisette Van", "last": "Gemert-Pijnen"}, {"first": "Stephen J", "last": "Bailey"}, {"first": "Wassim", "last": "Moalla"}, {"first": "Jonathan", "last": "Gómez-Raja"}, {"first": "Monique", "last": "Epstein"}, {"first": "Robbert", "last": "Sanderman"}, {"first": "Sebastian", "last": "Schulz"}, {"first": "Achim", "last": "Jerg"}, {"first": "Ramzi Al-", "last": "Horani"}, {"first": "Taysir", "last": "Mansi"}, {"first": "Mohamed", "last": "Jmail"}, {"first": "Fernando", "last": "Barbosa"}, {"first": "Fernando", "last": "Santos"}, {"first": "Boštjan", "last": "Šimunič"}, {"first": "Rado", "last": "Pišot"}, {"first": "Donald", "last": "Cowan"}, {"first": "Andrea", "last": "Gaggioli"}, {"first": "Jürgen", "last": "Steinacker"}, {"first": "Laurel", "last": "Riemann"}, {"first": "Bryan L", "last": "Riemann"}, {"first": "Notger", "last": "Mueller"}, {"first": "Tarak", "last": "Driss"}, {"first": "Anita", "last": "Hoekelmann"}], "abstract": "Public health recommendations and government measures during the COVID-19 pandemic have enforced restrictions on daily living, which may include social distancing, remote work/school, and home confinement. While these measures are imperative to abate the spreading of COVID-19, the impact of these restrictions on mental health and emotional wellbeing is undefined. Therefore, an international online survey was launched on April 6, 2020 in seven languages to elucidate the impact of COVID-19 restrictions on mental health and emotional well-being. This report presents the preliminary results from the first thousand responders on mental wellbeing and mood and feelings questionnaires.", "keywords": ["Public health", "Pandemic", "Mental wellbeing", "Depression"]}
